ciscoWpanMIB.name: ciscoWpanMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoWpanMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-cgr@cisco.com
ciscoWpanMIB.description: This MIB module defines management objects for configuration and monitoring of Wireless Personal Area Network (WPAN). Personal Area Network (PAN) is a network for interconnecting devices centered on an individual person's workspace. A Wireless Personal Area Network (WPAN) is a PAN in which the connections are wireless. WPAN is based on the standard IEEE 802.15.4. *** ABBREVIATIONS, ACRONYMS, AND SYMBOLS *** PAN - Personal Area Network RPL - IPv6 Routing Protocol for Low power and Lossy networks WPAN - Wireless Personal Area Network

cwpanInterfaceTable.name: cwpanInterfaceTable
cwpanInterfaceTable.description: This table contains a list of the WPAN interfaces on this device.

cwpanInterfaceEntry.name: cwpanInterfaceEntry
cwpanInterfaceEntry.description: An entry containing the management information for a particular WPAN interface. An entry is created when a WPAN interface has been added to ifTable. An entry is deleted when a WPAN interface has been removed from ifTable.

cwpanIfServiceStatus.name: cwpanIfServiceStatus
cwpanIfServiceStatus.description: This object indicates the status of WPAN service associated with this given interface. start (1) - WPAN service start stop (2) - WPAN service stop

cwpanIfServiceStatusReason.name: cwpanIfServiceStatusReason
cwpanIfServiceStatusReason.description: This object indicates the reason of the last state change of the WPAN service associated with this given interface. unknown (1) - unknown powerDown (2) - power down WPAN module powerUp (3) - power up WPAN module moduleRemove (4) - module removed moduleReload (5) - power cycle WPAN module driverStop (6) - driver stop driverStart (7) - driver start firmwareUpgrade (8) - firmware upgrade firmwareReset (9) - firmware reset watchDog (10) - watchdog triggered

cwpanIfRplTableResetReason.name: cwpanIfRplTableResetReason
cwpanIfRplTableResetReason.description: This object indicates the last reset reason of the WPAN RPL table associated with this given interface. unknown (1) - unknown manuallyClear (2) - RPL table was manually cleared configChange (3) - WPAN configuration changed interfaceDown (4) - WPAN interface was down timeout (5) - RPL table has not been updated for a long time serviceStop (6) - WPAN service has stopped

cwpanIfRplTableNodes.name: cwpanIfRplTableNodes
cwpanIfRplTableNodes.description: This object indicates the total number of entries in the WPAN RPL table for this given interface.

cwpanIfRplTableMajorThreshNodes.name: cwpanIfRplTableMajorThreshNodes
cwpanIfRplTableMajorThreshNodes.description: This object specifies the major node threshold for the WPAN RPL table. When the value of the corresponding instance of cwpanIfRplTableNodes is greater than this value, a cwpanRisingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif notification will be generated. After a cwpanRisingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif is generated, another such notification will not be generated if the value of the corresponding instance of cwpanIfRplTableNodes stays above this value. When the value of the corresponding instance of cwpanIfRplTableNodes becomes less than or equal to this value after a cwpanRisingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif notification is generated, a cwpanFallingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif notification will be generated. After a cwpanFallingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif is generated, another such notification will not be generated if the value of the corresponding instance of cwpanIfRplTableNodes does not exceed this value.

cwpanIfRplTableMinorThreshNodes.name: cwpanIfRplTableMinorThreshNodes
cwpanIfRplTableMinorThreshNodes.description: This object specifies the threshold for the RPL table nodes. When the value of the corresponding instance of cwpanIfRplTableNodes is greater than this threshold, a cwpanRisingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif notification will be generated. After a cwpanRisingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif is generated, another such notification will not be generated if the value of the corresponding instance of cwpanIfRplTableNodes stays above this threshold. When the value of the corresponding instance of cwpanIfRplTableNodes becomes less than or equal to this threshold after a cwpanRisingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif notification is generated, a cwpanFallingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif notification will be generated. After a cwpanFallingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif is generated, another such notification will not be generated if the value of the corresponding instance of cwpanIfRplTableNodes does not exceed this threshold.

cwpanNotificationEnable.name: cwpanNotificationEnable
cwpanNotificationEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates the following notifications: cwpanServiceStatusChangeNotif cwpanRplTableResetNotif cwpanRisingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif cwpanFallingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif cwpanRisingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif cwpanFallingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif A value of 'false' will prevent any of the above notifications from being generated by this system.

cwpanServiceStatusChangeNotif.name: cwpanServiceStatusChangeNotif
cwpanServiceStatusChangeNotif.description: This notification is generated if the WPAN service status has been changed.

cwpanRplTableResetNotif.name: cwpanRplTableResetNotif
cwpanRplTableResetNotif.description: This notification is generated if a WPAN RPL table has been reset.

cwpanRisingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif.name: cwpanRisingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif
cwpanRisingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif.description: This notification is generated if the number of nodes in the RPL table is greater than the threshold in cwpanIfRplTableMinorThreshNodes.

cwpanFallingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNoti.name: cwpanFallingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif
cwpanFallingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNoti.description: This notification is generated if the number of nodes in a RPL table become less than or equal to the cwpanIfRplTableMinorThreshNodes value after a cwpanRisingIfRplTblMinorThreshNodesNotif notification is generated.

cwpanRisingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif.name: cwpanRisingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif
cwpanRisingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif.description: This notification is generated if the number of nodes in a RPL table is greater than the value of cwpanIfRplTableMajorThreshNodes.

cwpanFallingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNoti.name: cwpanFallingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif
cwpanFallingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNoti.description: This notification is generated when the number of nodes in a RPL table become less than cwpanIfRplTableMajorThreshNodes value after a cwpanRisingIfRplTblMajorThreshNodesNotif notification is generated.

ciscoWpanMIBModuleCompliance.name: ciscoWpanMIBModuleCompliance
ciscoWpanMIBModuleCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the WPAN interface.

cwpanInterfaceInfoGroup.name: cwpanInterfaceInfoGroup
cwpanInterfaceInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the WPAN interface management information on the device.

cwpanNotificationControlGroup.name: cwpanNotificationControlGroup
cwpanNotificationControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing control of WPAN interface related notifications.

cwpanNotificationGroup.name: cwpanNotificationGroup
cwpanNotificationGroup.description: A collection of notifications for WPAN service and WPAN RPL table.
